Using a wrapping $if (not valid to BDScript 2)
If you get the error: Expected 2 numbers in X>NUM you can use a wrapping $if to bypass it
$if is executed before everything, therefore bypassing $onlyIf, $argsCheck and others, an easy way to bypass this error is to do the same checks those do, but with $if.

Example:
```
$if[$message[1]>2]
it's higher then 2
$else
it's lower then 2
$endif
```
The above code will error if you use a word instead of a number in $message[1], but here is how to bypass that:
```
$if[$isNumber[$message[1]]==true]
$if[$message[1]>2]
it's higher then 2
$else
it's lower then 2
$endif
$endif
```

Now the $if with $isNumber is used before the $if with the numbers, if you didn't provide a number as $message[1] the second $if won't run and therefore won't error.

<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig reset` - Resets the configuration.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig blacklist [add/remove]` - Add/Remove Blacklisted Roles.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig bypass [add/remove]` - Add/Remove Bypass Roles.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig multiplier [add/remove]` - Add/Remove Multiplier for Roles
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig emote [emote]` - Change the giveaway emote.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig banner [image url]/default/disable` - Configure the giveaway banner.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig color [color]/default` - Change the giveaway embed color.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig winrole [role]/none` - Change the role given to giveaway winners.
<:D_Arrow:776867851596070983> `gconfig pingrole [role]/none` - Change the role to be pinged for giveaways.
